.TH "HTMLTableRowElement.insertCell" "JS" "July 25, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLTableRowElement.insertCell \- HTMLTableRowElement: insertCell()
method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]insertCell()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]HTMLTableRowElement\f[R] interface inserts a new cell
(\f[CR]<td>\f[R]) into a table row (\f[CR]<tr>\f[R]) and returns a
reference to the cell.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] \f[CR]insertCell()\f[R] inserts the cell directly into
the row.
The cell does not need to be appended separately with
\f[CR]Node.appendChild()\f[R] as would be the case if
\f[CR]Document.createElement()\f[R] had been used to create the new
\f[CR]<td>\f[R] element.
.PP
You can not use \f[CR]insertCell()\f[R] to create a new \f[CR]<th>\f[R]
element though.
.RE
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
insertCell()
insertCell(index)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]index\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
The cell index of the new cell.
If \f[CR]index\f[R] is \f[CR]\-1\f[R] or equal to the number of cells,
the cell is appended as the last cell in the row.
If \f[CR]index\f[R] is omitted it defaults to \f[CR]\-1\f[R].
.SS Return value
An \f[CR]HTMLTableCellElement\f[R] that references the new cell.
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]IndexSizeError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if \f[CR]index\f[R] is greater than the number of cells.
.SH EXAMPLES
This example uses \f[CR]HTMLTableRowElement.insertCell()\f[R] to append
a new cell to a row.
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]table\f[R]>
  <\f[B]thead\f[R]>
    <\f[B]tr\f[R]>
      <\f[B]th\f[R]>C1</\f[B]th\f[R]>
      <\f[B]th\f[R]>C2</\f[B]th\f[R]>
      <\f[B]th\f[R]>C3</\f[B]th\f[R]>
      <\f[B]th\f[R]>C4</\f[B]th\f[R]>
      <\f[B]th\f[R]>C5</\f[B]th\f[R]>
    </\f[B]tr\f[R]>
  </\f[B]thead\f[R]>
  <\f[B]tbody\f[R]>
    <\f[B]tr\f[R]>
      <\f[B]td\f[R]>Cell 1</\f[B]td\f[R]>
      <\f[B]td\f[R]>Cell 2</\f[B]td\f[R]>
    </\f[B]tr\f[R]>
  </\f[B]tbody\f[R]>
</\f[B]table\f[R]>

<\f[B]button\f[R] id=\[dq]add\[dq]>Add a cell</\f[B]button\f[R]>
<\f[B]button\f[R] id=\[dq]remove\[dq]>Remove last cell</\f[B]button\f[R]>
<\f[B]div\f[R]>This first row has <\f[B]output\f[R]>2</\f[B]output\f[R]> cell(s).</\f[B]div\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
\f[I]// Obtain relevant interface elements\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] bodySection = document.querySelectorAll(\[dq]tbody\[dq])[0];
\f[B]const\f[R] row = bodySection.rows[0]; \f[I]// Select the first row of the body section\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] cells = row.cells; \f[I]// The collection is live, therefore always up\-to\-date\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] cellNumberDisplay = document.querySelectorAll(\[dq]output\[dq])[0];

\f[B]const\f[R] addButton = document.getElementById(\[dq]add\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] removeButton = document.getElementById(\[dq]remove\[dq]);

\f[B]function\f[R] updateCellNumber() {
  cellNumberDisplay.textContent = cells.length;
}

addButton.addEventListener(\[dq]click\[dq], () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[I]// Add a new cell at the end of the first row\f[R]
  \f[B]const\f[R] newCell = row.insertCell();
  newCell.textContent = \[ga]Cell ${cells.length}\[ga];

  \f[I]// Update the row counter\f[R]
  updateCellNumber();
});

removeButton.addEventListener(\[dq]click\[dq], () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[I]// Delete the row from the body\f[R]
  row.deleteCell(\-1);

  \f[I]// Update the row counter\f[R]
  updateCellNumber();
});
.EE
